summary: Customer service professional with extensive call center experience, strong training and development skills, and a focus on customer satisfaction. Demonstrated ability to manage teams, handle inquiries, resolve problems, and maintain accurate records in fast-paced environments.

experience.title: Patient Advocate
experience.description: Maintained patient records; observed and documented patient status; reported complaints to the case manager; managed calls in a fast-paced call center; set up patient appointments; kept conversation records; achieved appointment goals; answered questions about insurance and treatments.

experience.title: Insurance Agent
experience.description: Promoted agency products; calculated premiums and payment methods; interviewed clients to assess financial needs and existing coverage; processed applications, payments, endorsements and cancellations; met with walk-in policyholders; contacted warm leads; maintained activity and production logs.

experience.title: Debt Collector
experience.description: Handled inbound and outbound calls for past-due accounts; set up payment plans; managed high call volumes (up to 20 calls per minute); pursued daily monetary goals.

experience.title: CNA
experience.description: Assisted with patient care, documented medical history and vital signs, and supported mobility and daily living activities; provided transportation and companionship; assisted with transfers and ambulation; maintained cleanliness of living areas.
